statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.name: turnovers
statistics.description: The number of times a player loses possession to the other team.

statistics.name: minutes
statistics.description: The total number of minutes played.

statistics.name: assistTurnoverRatio
statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

statistics.name: rebounds
statistics.description: The total number of rebounds (offensive and defensive).

statistics.name: defensiveRebounds
statistics.description: The number of times when the defense obtains the possession of the ball after a missed shot by the offense.

article.headline: Youngstown St. 86, Wilberforce 51
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio -- Damian Eargle scored 16 points and Devonte Maymon added 15 to lead Youngstown State to an 86-51 win over Wilberforce on Tuesday night. The Penguins (7-9) pulled away easily from Wilberforce of the NAIA, despite shooting 39.5 percent (32 of 81) from the floor. Youngstown State dominated on the boards, outrebounding Wilberforce 61-42. Kendrick Perry finished with 13 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists for the Penguins, who ended a three-game losing streak. DuShawn Brooks had eight points and 11 rebounds. Youngstown State went into halftime with a 39-26 advantage. The Penguins pushed their lead to 30 points 10:24 left in the second half, highlighted by Perry's dunk off his steal. Tremayne Scott scored 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for Wilberforce (2-13), which made 32.3 percent (20 of 62) of its field goal attempts. Darius Foster also had 15 points.
